<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="816" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115(39) City of Flint/34:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-26T00:00:00+03:00">October
                                    26, 1939—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received October 26—6:20
                                p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>808. My 807, October 26, 11 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>]. The
                            Soviet radio at 11:30 p.m., announced that after examination of her
                            cargo the naval authorities have decided to release the <hi rend="italic">City of Flint</hi> on condition that she leave the
                            port of Murmansk immediately.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>